definition: station/to stand/to halt/to stop/branch of a company or organization/website

sentences.english: These parts of Ord Mantell are not intended for tourists.
sentences.chinese: 曼特尔兵站的这些部分无意接待游客。

sentences.english: Several bounty hunters almost succeeded in collecting during run-ins on Ord Mantell.
sentences.chinese: 几个赏金猎人在曼特尔兵站与汉遭遇，差点得手。

sentences.english: The surveyor heaved a sigh and made his way out of the station.
sentences.chinese: 土地测量员叹了口气，离开了兵站。

sentences.english: Ord Mantell has some of the most lenient banking laws in the galaxy.
sentences.chinese: 曼特尔兵站拥有某些银河系中最宽松的银行法律。

sentences.english: The military depot has a plentiful supply of food.
sentences.chinese: 这个兵站有富足的食品供应。

sentences.english: The rules of "comfort Station" stipulated by the depot headquarters.
sentences.chinese: 日军兵站司令部制定的《慰安所规定》。

sentences.english: Ord Mantell attracts about a billion tourists annually.
sentences.chinese: 每年，曼特尔兵站吸引大约十亿游客。
